    <h2> Introducing Jasmine-jQuery</h2>
    <aside class="notes">
    There's 
    jasmine-jquery which provides two extensions for Jasmine JavaScript Testing Framework:

<li> a set of custom matchers for jQuery framework </li>
<li> an API for handling HTML, CSS, and JSON fixtures in your specs</li>
</aside>
